news.title: PAG, Mapletree to buy Hong Kong's Goldin Financial Global Centre for $713 million
news.para: Goldin Financial Global Centre is located in Kowloon East and was completed in 2016 with a total lettable area of 886,703 square feet (82,377 square metres), PAG and Mapletree said in a statement.

news.title: Swedish single-family house prices fall 5% in Q4 2022
news.para: Prices of single-family homes have tumbled this year on soaring inflation and repeated big rate hikes by the Swedish Central Bank, breaking a decades-long boom in real estate prices that jacked up household debts to among the highest levels in Europe.

news.title: Clarify details on notice for demolition: Andhra Pradesh HC tells MAUD
news.para: The high court found fault with the existing guidelines issued by the state government noting that the GO lacks clarity as to whom the reply should be given and who will give final orders.

news.title: Kamdhenu Ventures to list on stock exchanges this month: Group CMD
news.para: There are plans to raise Rs 200 crore through multiple routes and expand the paints business post listing, the CMD said. The group also aims to garner a revenue of Rs 1,000 crore from the paints segment over the next five years, he said.

news.title: CCTV cameras to be must at city homes soon: Assam CM
news.para: “CCTVs may not prevent crimes but can act as a deterrant and certainly would help in detecting crimes,” CM Himanta Biswa Sarma said after reviewing the city’s crime situation at the police headquarters here on Wednesday.

news.title: Trezi raises over $2 million in series-A round from new & existing investors
news.para: Trezi will utilise the funding to accelerate its platform development in the metaverse and accelerate its entry into high-potential new geographies.

news.title: Realty norms near defence units a worry for Pune civic body, PCMC
news.para: The Dakshin Maharashtra & Goa Sub Area, the local military authority in Pune, has constituted a board of officers to survey the defence installations that are of security interest vis-à-vis the revised norms.

news.title: Visakhapatnam civic body commissioner says it will raze illegal constructions
news.para: P Raja Babu made it clear that the unauthorised structures will be demolished by the corporation. In an official statement issued on Wednesday.

news.title: Citco pays Rs 1.4 crore property tax to Chandigarh civic body
news.para: Significantly, the tax paid by the Citco is the highest from any one department in the current financial year. The amount includes arrears.

news.title: Flawed software affects Thiruvananthapuram corporation's property tax database
news.para: In some cases, buildings for which tax has been paid would be shown as demolished or non-existent, much to the shock of the taxpayers.

news.title: Tirupur civic body makes list of property tax defaulters public
news.para: The list is published on the city corporation’s official website. According to an official, some defaulters owe the civic body Rs13 lakh to Rs94 lakh in property tax, which they failed to pay up to the second quarter of the current financial year.

news.title: Over three lakh houses under PMAY-Gramin approved in Assam
news.para: "In the last one week, the Panchayat and Rural Development Department of Assam has been able to sanction 3,04,218 houses to the beneficiaries," he added.

news.title: Cidco cancels sale of disputed Nerul CRZ plot
news.para: Cidco informed the National Green Tribunal (NGT), in its additional affidavit, that the auction was cancelled as the bidding offer received for the 25,139 square metre plot was far below the prevailing market rate.

news.title: West Bengal to take back unutilised leased-out land from industrialists
news.para: The cabinet also decided to reward those industrialists who have set up factories on leased-out land by converting their land-lease to "unconditional deed".

news.title: Societies in Ahmedabad approach original builders for redevelopment work
news.para: Decades-old developer groups like Bakeri, Synthesis and Ami Corporation have received some proposals for redevelopment from their old societies.
